item.description:
 &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;github.com/golang-migrate/migrate&#34;&gt;Go-migrate&lt;/a&gt; is a simple and easy to use database migration (schema evolution) library for go with good support for many mainstream databases. This post is a quick recipe on how we can bundle the migrations (sql patch files) within our go binary - this is particularly helpful when the app is distributed a single binary without dependencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Go stdlib includes an &lt;a href=&#34;https://pkg.go.dev/embed&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener external nofollow noreferrer&#34;&gt;embed package&lt;/a&gt; that simplifies accessing files embedded in the running go program. Also go-migrate has support for httpfs as a source that makes it easy to integrate the two.&lt;/p&gt;
